</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"f9054ed1ca8a"><strong>Important:</strong> Always set the <st=
rong>Timezone</strong> field to match your property's timezone (e.g. <code>=
Europe/Prague</code>). If left empty, the schedule will use GMT, which may =
cause the automation to run at unexpected times.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"1f560afc3533" id=3D"GettingStartedwithMewsAutomations-Each(=
Loop)=E2=80=94utility">Each (Loop) =E2=80=94 utility</h3>
<p local-id=3D"36b126dc277a">The <strong>Each</strong> component loops over=
 a list and processes each item individually. It takes a list as input and =
outputs one item at a time to the connected downstream component(s). This i=
s essential when a previous component returns multiple items (e.g. a list o=
f reservation IDs) and you need to perform an action on each one.</p><span =
class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-e=
mbedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image image-center" =
alt=3D"image-20260429-132324.png" width=3D"407" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"ac9=
484ef7fb481dbcc82c93904041827117ec4a2db5322cf974b20faabd284c1" data-image-s=
rc=3D"https://mews.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932100130/image=
-20260429-132324.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1777469005830&amp;c=
acheVersion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data-height=3D"566" data-width=3D"407" data-u=
nresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1931805324" data-l=
inked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-=
linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image-20260429-132324.png" data-base-url=
=3D"https://mews.atlassian.net/wiki" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"i=
mage/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1932100130" data-linked-reso=
urce-container-version=3D"8" data-media-id=3D"75826082-4269-4adb-97ee-62a96=
75508e4" data-media-type=3D"file" height=3D"565"></span>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"a1=
cc5775-85f8-4499-a1b6-d40f61e56c88" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"100aca34-d47d-4096-995b-7aade878eeed">
<th data-local-id=3D"2d591ed5-97c5-48c9-adfc-5183c05292f6" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"ae7a1f3bb6cf">Field</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"37b75f83-9483-49d6-b4eb-91431283aaf6" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"403a07640b69">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"b26bdb1e-65a6-41a5-a2ee-4ab25eb2486b">
<td data-local-id=3D"77003715-27e1-40b3-88e3-5fc76fe9ecb9" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"03ec9968ebc8"><strong>Field</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"e4d07cf5-63ab-43b1-a3d2-3cf9d8d79e25" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"231695963da1">The list you want to iterate over. Click <stro=
ng>+</strong> to select the list output from a previous component (e.g. Res=
ervation IDs from Get Eligible Arrivals).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"8c89f88a-0103-41a5-ad83-373f5394770f">
<td data-local-id=3D"6c541e75-4ffb-47fc-bd47-b8622f14c496" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f572b92be596"><strong>Delay</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"963fbe13-8802-4564-b617-53e2ce6da0db" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"60d15ba45584">Optional delay between items in milliseconds. =
Useful to avoid overwhelming external systems with rapid-fire requests.</p>=
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"78701b1bf735"><strong>How it works:</strong> If Get Eligible=
 Arrivals returns 5 reservation IDs, the Each component will fire 5 times, =
passing one reservation ID each time to the connected downstream components=
. The downstream components (e.g. Upgrade Room, Send SMS) will therefore ex=
ecute once per reservation.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"ef9eb17b3a22" id=3D"GettingStartedwithMewsAutomations-Condi=
tion(If/Else)=E2=80=94utility">Condition (If/Else) =E2=80=94 utility</h3>
<p local-id=3D"f053b49ecb6a">The <strong>Condition</strong> component lets =
you add branching logic to your automation. It evaluates a condition and ro=
utes the flow down one of two paths: <strong>True</strong> or <strong>False=
</strong>.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"4b=
9d154c-dc64-4db8-b0b7-c4358527babe" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"f99b82f4-8fc0-479f-847f-12649e01d462">
<th data-local-id=3D"cbe9603a-2634-4128-b957-9e022266b5a4" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"612dd676a541">Field</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"c9555e4a-37c4-4d58-bbb3-c30c6e617746" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"a850f2556f11">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"898eff52-9947-4c96-b02a-b459d8a4393b">
<td data-local-id=3D"379364c4-ca99-40d3-9d73-089022fea6a0" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"1f4b08b856d1"><strong>Input value</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"307f9ee1-ad47-47a0-bd62-3301be3ab77a" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"970cddf37591">The value to check (use the <strong>+</strong>=
 picker to reference a variable).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"126b471a-41b7-4019-b7c2-f7d8a31b1d79">
<td data-local-id=3D"c35ec400-7b14-49a5-a7e9-3b3a6bd2d371" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"cff285f50cf0"><strong>Operator</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"0273e236-8fb2-4182-97f4-71368924d874" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a4802ad6ced3">The comparison: equals, not equals, contains, =
greater than, less than, is empty, etc.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"3541536e-002f-43b0-a326-1e4919017f6b">
<td data-local-id=3D"da7b34a1-f33b-4124-b0a0-20cbe59d723e" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a51b2e95cac0"><strong>Comparison value</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"18d82a60-c855-433e-a369-dbfa002c9bae" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e4417d8adddc">The value to compare against.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"db5839745e0a">The component has two output ports: one for th=
e <strong>True</strong> path and one for the <strong>False</strong> path. C=
onnect different downstream components to each path.</p>
<p local-id=3D"7a74a8d6250e"><strong>Example:</strong> Check if the occupan=
cy percentage is below 80%. If True =E2=86=92 proceed with room upgrades. I=
f False =E2=86=92 skip upgrades (the property is too full).</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"be00098e285c" id=3D"GettingStartedwithMewsAutomations-Delay=
=E2=80=94utility">Delay =E2=80=94 utility</h3>
<p local-id=3D"38fb2c002687">The <strong>Delay</strong> component pauses th=
e automation for a specified amount of time before continuing to the next s=
tep. Useful when you need to wait between actions.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"eb=
f61361-8e79-4602-b6e0-9a3c151c1acb" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"3f3a6d6f-e214-4214-9fbf-d286b1aa2dd4">
<th data-local-id=3D"4a7b0861-383d-47f9-84db-2629888b086f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"cbd45748c6a7">Field</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"b0c63ac9-1112-4740-8b9e-a897994eda53" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"059e5d07d39f">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"d8c9fae4-da95-4920-9694-1cc042e13341">
<td data-local-id=3D"c139c1f2-c3d4-424e-96e7-1c7d070a6c0f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"92a8a26dbde7"><strong>Duration</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7dca7a9b-72ef-4291-b185-aa3b2373da3b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"767046c24b1f">The amount of time to wait (in seconds or mill=
iseconds, depending on configuration).</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"55b69e262bfc" id=3D"GettingStartedwithMewsAutomations-SetVa=
riable=E2=80=94utility">Set Variable =E2=80=94 utility</h3>
<p local-id=3D"94295fb07718">The <strong>Set Variable</strong> component le=
ts you create a named variable that stores a value or a transformed result.=
 This is useful when you need to reuse the same computed value in multiple =
downstream components without repeating the transformation.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"911c8c00-86d5-4a89-92fe-0baf6e09c933">
<h2 local-id=3D"668c776f6bb1" id=3D"GettingStartedwithMewsAutomations-14.St=
arting,Stopping,andTestingYourAutomation">14. Starting, Stopping, and Testi=
ng Your Automation</h2>
<p local-id=3D"9b338d0d5e19">Once your automation is built and configured, =
you need to <strong>start</strong> it for it to begin running.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"8df8a77583a1" id=3D"GettingStartedwithMewsAutomations-Start=
inganautomation">Starting an automation</h3>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"811264ed-88ce-4c13-b766-792fa84d8fb8">
<li local-id=3D"0d13cb0d-e1cd-44a5-8bfe-afa734b244a6">
<p local-id=3D"37ab63d03a9d">In the flow designer, click the <strong>Start<=
/strong> button (typically a play icon in the top toolbar).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2c888a4e-82ca-4a69-ab7e-b7f9dc0d0325">
<p local-id=3D"4eda6643d6d8">The automation status will change to <strong>A=
ctive</strong>.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"503be001-787e-421e-aa94-3f42bd18b402">
<p local-id=3D"27d723cd4186">If the trigger is event-based (e.g. Reservatio=
n Created), the automation will wait for that event to occur.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"61c1059f-3e2b-42bd-80bf-d03db35af136">
<p local-id=3D"2462a7d419a3">If the trigger is a Cron Scheduler, the automa=
tion will run at the next scheduled time. If <strong>Trigger immediately</s=
trong> is set to True, it will also run once right away.</p></li>
</ol>
<h3 local-id=3D"6f0432c49650" id=3D"GettingStartedwithMewsAutomations-Stopp=
inganautomation">Stopping an automation</h3>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"79d4a6a0-f5d2-4aa1-888a-e672536f6f37">
<li local-id=3D"0f026aac-eddd-4886-a9df-872d42c4ee66">
<p local-id=3D"98e603beaf34">Click the <strong>Stop</strong> button in the =
flow designer toolbar.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"dcea37b4-2689-4eb8-b66c-81133b956577">
<p local-id=3D"27b237171a29">The automation status will change to <strong>I=
nactive</strong>.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"066d6234-0b68-4587-a762-53feb75df92f">
<p local-id=3D"2395df035fc2">No further triggers will fire until the automa=
tion is started again.</p></li>
</ol>
<h3 local-id=3D"2f2850822c4c" id=3D"GettingStartedwithMewsAutomations-Testi=
ngyourautomation">Testing your automation</h3>
<p local-id=3D"c11b2064d0bc"><strong>Tip:</strong> Before starting an autom=
ation in production, it's a good practice to test it. Here are some approac=
hes:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"6800839a-d16c-48d1-b14b-e2a7b0e72c72">
<li local-id=3D"d1fcb49b-fcbc-4481-9a4a-f118de5e8914">
<p local-id=3D"c9d74b46a2a9"><strong>Use "Trigger immediately":</strong> Fo=
r Cron Scheduler-based automations, set the "Trigger immediately" toggle to=
 True. This will run the automation once as soon as you start it, so you ca=
n verify the results without waiting for the next scheduled time.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3e565f9c-0131-4c80-ac51-e9294f3472e1">
<p local-id=3D"079f0b52a84a"><strong>Check the Action Log:</strong> After a=
 test run, switch to the <strong>Action log</strong> tab on the Automations=
 dashboard to see what happened. You can verify which components executed, =
what data flowed through, and whether any errors occurred.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"441e4362-1c38-4fa0-a391-f2d0a3d83360">
<p local-id=3D"d6ca015bf5df"><strong>Start with a small scope:</strong> Use=
 restrictive filters (e.g. a specific loyalty tier) so your test only affec=
ts a small number of reservations.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"89069603-18ce-43ca-a9ed-2237ad0b16be">
<h2 local-id=3D"7d0641fa1d9f" id=3D"GettingStartedwithMewsAutomations-15.Th=
eActionLog">15. The Action Log</h2>
<p local-id=3D"47c5490cbbba">The <strong>Action log</strong> tab on the Aut=
omations dashboard provides a chronological record of every action executed=
 by your automations. It is your primary tool for monitoring and debugging.=
</p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper co=
nfluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image imag=
e-center" alt=3D"image-20260429-132442.png" width=3D"468" loading=3D"lazy" =
src=3D"52e30b9ac2ef7e1d67992110888fbae3da267e50f5f1f09eb287a97c9bc95268" da=
ta-image-src=3D"https://mews.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/193210=
0130/image-20260429-132442.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D177746908=
4678&amp;cacheVersion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data-height=3D"1205" data-width=3D"=
2006" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"193170=
7271" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attac=
hment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image-20260429-132442.png" dat=
a-base-url=3D"https://mews.atlassian.net/wiki" data-linked-resource-content=
-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1932100130" data-l=
inked-resource-container-version=3D"8" data-media-id=3D"a653ab4d-9bd8-4a0c-=
9b74-a6f45a16cee1" data-media-type=3D"file" height=3D"281"></span>
<p local-id=3D"13e0229816bc">Use the Action log to:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"28cdfe16-2352-4622-924d-4230a86efeba">
<li local-id=3D"ed461b76-4b12-4cbe-9cfd-d1869ba1239b">
<p local-id=3D"3cef7d2da920"><strong>Verify execution:</strong> Confirm tha=
t your automation ran when expected.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9acb6a31-8082-40c5-9689-0d3da14cee6e">
<p local-id=3D"064c6eb8a2ce"><strong>Debug issues:</strong> Identify which =
component in the flow caused an error.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"178416c0-c745-4556-b561-42d65b92fe19">
<p local-id=3D"0dbc4652a77d"><strong>Review data:</strong> See what data wa=
s passed between components during execution.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f380e547-1322-4443-a291-5cb3d6d4ba15">
<p local-id=3D"03d1654ff6e5"><strong>Track activity:</strong> Monitor how o=
ften your automations are running and what actions they're performing.</p><=
/li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"eba3f98e-cba1-42fb-93d0-f204fb80a2e9">
<h2 local-id=3D"ec18bfd57e39" id=3D"GettingStartedwithMewsAutomations-16.Us=
ingTemplates">16. Using Templates</h2>
<p local-id=3D"2e4d5257edd2">Templates are pre-built automations designed f=
or common hospitality workflows. They save you time by providing a fully co=
nfigured flow that you can use as-is or customize.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"b0055392f5b9" id=3D"GettingStartedwithMewsAutomations-Avail=
abletemplates">Available templates</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"57=
efccb5-a9bf-4b92-8970-761eb85f81f1" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"fc51f47e-7aca-4df4-b102-d9462a8a6754">
<th data-local-id=3D"d4eb1dfe-5f4e-4e53-99bf-d83ea1a044e0" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"a18ce3546070">Template</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"42fdfd6f-12f2-437e-bd96-07a716b64a01" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"7cd149bfc97b">Description</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"944d23c7-33f8-4471-b17a-d05fb6b57bef" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"ed12c6ca36ef">Trigger</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"7784e100-0aca-4e5e-aef1-4085c5eeba42">
<td data-local-id=3D"d5f5c204-c75c-4a3c-8236-d13f28fd674a" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f4495e187fe9"><strong>Upgrade room for loyalty members</stro=
ng></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"6cbdbcb8-8872-4640-b274-f408cfb5f049" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"88a30c25515a">Runs daily. Identifies arriving guests with op=
tional loyalty/behavioral filters, checks property occupancy, attempts room=
 upgrades based on configured upgrade paths and availability buffers, sends=
 an SMS to upgraded guests, and adds a note to reservations where the upgra=
de failed.</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"28220824-bfb5-4785-8b2c-a6cd5618c26f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b6dcc8331f52">Cron Scheduler (daily)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"ecfe0f3e-ea4b-4daf-afe9-4cb9e8b5984a">
<td data-local-id=3D"fc87c4cf-a313-48bf-935e-329d7bed4a3b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"550aa15bd23f"><strong>Welcome gift for VIP guests</strong></=
p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"ae311965-8846-473d-9cb8-5a180088c8eb" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3ef1c6e3ce29">Runs daily. Identifies arriving guests, checks=
 which gift products are compatible with each reservation's service, create=
s a task in Mews Operations for your team to prepare the gift, and sends an=
 SMS notification to the guest.</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"98b751d5-2635-48f4-9230-114e15444922" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"59a2e09a30d5">Cron Scheduler (daily)</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"82b2dfcbef31" id=3D"GettingStartedwithMewsAutomations-Howto=
useatemplate">How to use a template</h3>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"f55bfec0-6467-4ec7-a4a2-b57d3fb587f8">
<li local-id=3D"29944472-2bac-48f5-8495-852319432dfd">
<p local-id=3D"6848e9a7ceef">Click <strong>+ Create</strong> on the Automat=
ions dashboard.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"729a12bb-ef51-4b11-b0e7-72c28b625dcb">
<p local-id=3D"e34e03dfbb2b">Select a template from the list (e.g. <strong>=
Upgrade room for loyalty members</strong>).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"613ee114-eb99-4a5f-bc0e-f0592cf8f25b">
<p local-id=3D"8acd5ff89113">The flow designer opens with all components pr=
e-placed and connected.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4bef4469-796c-4fe3-93aa-28cd55e15e17">
<p local-id=3D"efeeff90cab2">Review each component's settings in the Inspec=
tor panel. Most fields come pre-filled with sensible defaults.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c785cb05-555d-4063-821f-d5ecdca7a6fb">
<p local-id=3D"49f21381a258">Adjust any required fields specific to your pr=
operty (these are highlighted in the template documentation).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"803c8478-6d36-4923-b639-4d4693610c0c">
<p local-id=3D"6ad6291e68f9">Click <strong>Start</strong> when you're ready=
.</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"b211104665e1"><strong>Note:</strong> For step-by-step setup =
instructions and detailed configuration guides for each template, see the d=
edicated template documentation pages.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"51a5c622-0d5a-478b-90d5-b1b88ecd5bad">
<h2 local-id=3D"c1a42add10e0" id=3D"GettingStartedwithMewsAutomations-17.Be=
stPractices">17. Best Practices</h2>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"da909ebe-5d08-4f1a-8831-3a8757087057">
<li local-id=3D"ed929488-bfba-4868-b62f-9eba41902ff8">
<p local-id=3D"4d0545a71ad7"><strong>Start with a template.</strong> Even i=
f your use case is different, templates provide a great example of how to s=
tructure a flow and connect components.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"79b2f805-ba26-46dd-9f0f-9b9f83ad3b47">
<p local-id=3D"0c8446e9e85b"><strong>Name your automations clearly.</strong=
> Use descriptive names like "Morning room upgrade for gold members" rather=
 than "Untitled" so you and your team can quickly identify what each automa=
tion does.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e271346b-3569-403c-abea-6e6790edfe75">
<p local-id=3D"484b1838cabd"><strong>Set the timezone on Cron Schedulers.</=
strong> Always configure the timezone field to match your property's timezo=
ne so automations run at the expected local time.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a931bbaa-8172-4761-8fd7-0542dda360d8">
<p local-id=3D"2ecfe540fa02"><strong>Test with small scope first.</strong> =
Use filters to limit your automation to a small set of reservations during =
testing (e.g. a specific loyalty tier or a single date). Once confirmed, br=
oaden the scope.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8ada203f-de6b-47cf-9277-315ab03dfada">
<p local-id=3D"f9df0b167157"><strong>Use the Action log regularly.</strong>=
 After starting a new automation, check the Action log to confirm it's runn=
ing correctly and producing the expected results.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c00253e9-b8c8-4bb7-9305-0b47fee9d808">
<p local-id=3D"35594434f77a"><strong>Add delays in loops.</strong> When usi=
ng the Each component to iterate over a large list, add a small delay betwe=
en items (e.g. 500=E2=80=931000 ms) to avoid overwhelming the system.</p></=
li>
<li local-id=3D"b84b13d1-abc1-48c4-ac3b-7ec969bae41e">
<p local-id=3D"a624cac8877a"><strong>Use modifiers instead of extra compone=
nts.</strong> If you need to transform a single value (e.g. format a date, =
concatenate strings), use modifiers on the variable rather than adding addi=
tional components. This keeps your flow cleaner.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5e2ab932-0589-4763-b4b2-309ce2e3b139">
<p local-id=3D"8559368d5db9"><strong>Keep automations focused.</strong> It'=
s better to have two simple automations than one overly complex one. If a w=
orkflow has many branches, consider splitting it into separate automations.=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5b1459c6-1daf-41cc-8387-f72eba72b66c">
<p local-id=3D"217f5c916ce3"><strong>Review before going live.</strong> Wal=
k through each component's configuration before starting the automation. Ve=
rify that all Required fields are filled, variables are correctly mapped, a=
nd the flow logic makes sense.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0bd3be2a-28ba-4671-a5aa-4317a1b5118d">
<p local-id=3D"2a672c253234"><strong>Document your automations.</strong> Us=
e the automation name and any internal notes or descriptions to record what=
 the automation does, who created it, and when it was last reviewed.</p></l=
i>
</ol>
<hr local-id=3D"5a4902dd-46ee-47da-a111-0869dc96acba">
<h2 local-id=3D"c180f3c5c2d0" id=3D"GettingStartedwithMewsAutomations-18.Tr=
oubleshooting">18. Troubleshooting</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"92=
220552-b249-4fce-9f9c-7f5c475455ff" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"71177a21-0b92-46aa-9493-1eec03529885">
<th data-local-id=3D"c762f043-dc6d-4e9d-82cd-bc47b6f6ace9" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"9476ec615c24">Problem</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"6a08b7a5-25ea-424a-a09d-a8ea2ed289e9" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"058d92ee5db3">Solution</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"9ff739b7-e8e1-4430-b41d-66b77f71ec92">
<td data-local-id=3D"71843452-274b-4361-acf4-510feb03c799" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5ff17e0f9b8f">My automation is not running</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"b540e225-1fc5-4e41-acc4-161a311d441a" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"14a805bea81d">Check that the automation status is <strong>Ac=
tive</strong>. If it uses a Cron Scheduler, verify the cron settings and ti=
mezone are correct. Check if "Trigger immediately" can help you test it rig=
ht away.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"42d87ba5-eb6b-4441-b27b-c8e2fe5f80d0">
<td data-local-id=3D"4bf2f770-d6b9-465a-ba1e-dc6bd6b90c51" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"76d5a5fa011e">The automation runs but nothing happens</p></t=
d>
<td data-local-id=3D"02f6d0b8-19c0-43ee-a8d0-e2552e1e4935" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"57165f9bd043">Check the <strong>Action log</strong> for erro=
rs. Verify that the trigger is producing output (e.g. there are actual arri=
vals for the date). Ensure all Required fields are filled in each component=
.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"ce5de28f-4519-4ed6-91ff-a79f55ec83d9">
<td data-local-id=3D"99c311b3-da95-4072-bd1b-6c6434d86acf" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"11429197332c">I see errors in the Action log</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"489e5ccb-e498-4919-9d4f-aa828f45c1e4" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"cad4bde21ef2">Click on the error entry to see the details. C=
ommon causes: a Required field is missing a value, a variable reference poi=
nts to a component that has no output data, or a downstream system is tempo=
rarily unavailable.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"65df915b-22a0-4705-bad4-ecbc99248645">
<td data-local-id=3D"d031a7e0-b452-44fc-8b61-8ea10a64f1f0" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"198fd3488f38">Variables show as empty at runtime</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"e586f0f6-a1a2-4066-a18e-bd3e06626169" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b1a1b254dbde">Make sure the upstream component is producing =
data. If it's a data retrieval component (e.g. Get Eligible Arrivals), veri=
fy that there is data to return (e.g. there are confirmed arrivals for toda=
y). Also check that the variable mapping in the <strong>+</strong> picker p=
oints to the correct output field.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"ac27ee29-0c0b-4c0f-b9ae-f35fd04db67c">
<td data-local-id=3D"e8c0ef12-fda8-4c07-a7e7-2b95bedd2bbe" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"895fcdc1b64f">The Cron Scheduler fires at the wrong time</p>=
</td>
<td data-local-id=3D"c3f42efe-99e1-4f8c-a971-94b896d08efd" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e45582f3a12e">Check the <strong>Timezone</strong> field. If =
it's empty, the scheduler defaults to GMT. Set it to your property's timezo=
ne (e.g. <code>Europe/Prague</code>, <code>America/New_York</code>).</p></t=
d>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"c5fe0847-62c7-417f-b9cf-e7ec0ec17900">
<td data-local-id=3D"2769e86c-043a-4f5d-915c-8f7e39765424" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"1bcfba45970a">The Each loop processes zero items</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"accc2996-69dc-41ca-b52b-b5b4eeedfe11" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c788ad683e46">Verify that the list variable connected to the=
 Each component is not empty. Check the previous component's output in the =
Action log. The list field must reference an array, not a single value.</p>=
</td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"9ea45e8e-d8d2-4156-bc69-658c4de52039">
<td data-local-id=3D"6e6afbf5-c6c7-46e0-acb0-09e974a52756" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"603e2f2f5c8d">SMS messages are not being sent</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"964e40f8-4e5a-4c11-8101-b5f9e299bf20" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b3747bc005e9">Verify that the guest has a valid phone number=
 in their profile. Check that the SMS component is correctly connected and =
the phone number variable is properly mapped.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"2421d83b-2b17-45f0-b658-d80fefeb759b">
<td data-local-id=3D"4304f4cf-64db-4cbc-b300-ad2a437d06e6" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"766b4ef757a1">I can't find a component in the palette</p></t=
d>
<td data-local-id=3D"f1c501c0-270a-4c34-ae4a-d9fc8aee1b77" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2210853af8be">Use the <strong>search bar</strong> at the top=
 of the component palette. Try different keywords (e.g. search "note" to fi=
nd "Add Note to Reservation"). Some components may be listed under differen=
t names than expected.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr local-id=3D"1de5ebb1-ced3-428c-b089-caca78701a43">
<h2 local-id=3D"513af3f08345" id=3D"GettingStartedwithMewsAutomations-What'=
sNext?">What's Next?</h2>
<p local-id=3D"2c3dbd97dfae">Now that you understand the basics, here are s=
ome next steps:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"64bd874d-7c26-45d2-bef5-7aa38b4d3fb1">
<li local-id=3D"b5851a8d-f6ac-426d-8b02-836eafe60e8e">
<p local-id=3D"94b7777f7178"><strong>Create your first automation</strong> =
using a template =E2=80=94 the <em>Welcome Gift for VIP Guests</em> templat=
e is a great starting point.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"bf7ccd5b-df16-410b-8f4f-38c86b2e27f3">
<p local-id=3D"5d8dbed0f9f9"><strong>Read the component documentation</stro=
ng> for each Mews component to understand all available input fields and op=
tions.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b7ef7295-0249-4e53-8998-39a4aa7a2ca2">
<p local-id=3D"6d2721a7d0ab"><strong>Experiment on the canvas</strong> =E2=
=80=94 create a custom automation with a Cron Scheduler trigger and a simpl=
e action to familiarize yourself with the flow designer.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4f4158d4-5073-4399-8b00-3fcf6c4dd689">
<p local-id=3D"75203ffd8729"><strong>Explore modifiers</strong> =E2=80=94 o=
pen the Modify variable panel and try chaining modifiers together to see ho=
w data transformations work.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"eb14b6ec8e70"><strong>You're ready!</strong> With Mews Autom=
ations, you can streamline your property's operations, deliver personalized=
 guest experiences, and free your team to focus on what matters most =E2=80=
=94 your guests. Happy automating!</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
